fr24feed changelog

All notable changes to Flightradar24 feeder software will be documented in this file.

The format is based on Keep a Changelog.

[1.0.25-3] - 2020-03-31

Added

  • Support for new extended Mode-S data fields

    Changed

  • Fixed settings not being saved on some installations.

  • Local IP now fetched with API calls rather than system commands.

[1.0.25-1] - 2020-03-10

Fixed

  • NIC decoding for ADS-B version 1 & 2

  • Settings were not writable when running Pi24 image

  • CRC checksum is now always enabled even when using basestation-tcp receiver.

    Added

  • Added incremental back off when MLAT connection cannot be established

[1.0.24-6] - 2019-11-04

Added

  • Local buffer for low-latency data

[1.0.24-4] - 2019-10-09

Fixed

  • Fixed Radarcape timestamp checking
  • Fixed avr-tcp receiver mode in no-mlat setting

[1.0.24-2] - 2019-10-01

Changed

  • Raspberry Pi debian package auto update now scheduled at random time on each receiver.

[1.0.24-1] - 2019-10-01

Fixed

  • Kinetic receiver support (SBS1,2,3 working again)

    Changed

  • Updated NTP synchronisation, custom server now possible with –ntp-server=

  • Decoder now uses c-ares for DNS, replaces system ping command for static build

[1.0.23-8] - 2018-10-11

Changed

  • Larger and configurable timeout for HTTP/HTTPS requests

[1.0.23-7] - 2018-09-28

Fixed

  • Report correct statistics on ADS-B / non-ADS-B tracked aircraft

[1.0.23-6] - 2018-09-26

Added

  • Autodetect GPS hardware info

[1.0.23-5] - 2018-09-14

Changed

  • Honor option for fallback to http

[1.0.23-4] - 2018-09-10

Changed

  • Fixes to use hard float on raspberry pi 3
  • Enable hardware flow control on Skysense model

[1.0.23-3] - 2018-09-07

Changed

  • Use https for signup

[1.0.23-2] - 2018-09-07

Changed

  • Skysense FPGA interface improvements

[1.0.23-1] - 2018-09-04

Changed

  • periodically fetch new configuration

[1.0.22-2] - 2018-08-29

Added

  • fr24feed backend support for new web interface

[1.0.22-1] - 2018-08-23

Added

  • Support for new Skysense model

[1.0.21-1] - 2018-08-15

Added

  • libcurl for HTTP requests

Removed

  • Windows builds

[1.0.20-1] - 2018-07-27

Added

  • Enhanced ModeS Derived Data Improvements

Removed

  • OSX builds

[1.0.19-15] - 2018-02-06

Fixed

  • fixed crash on locking after a certain interval [Windows]
  • connect to piaware raw data port 30005 only if it is open [Linux]

Added

  • monitor DNS and NTP queries count [all platforms]
  • monitor number of open file descriptors [Linux]
  • display local IPs on the web interface :8754 [Linux]

Changed

  • do not use jQuery on the web interface :8754 [all platforms]

[1.0.19-13] - 2018-02-01

Changed

  • moved directory creation steps into a separate script on fr24feed start [debian ARM]

[1.0.19-12] - 2018-01-31

Changed

  • use dark theme for web interface on port :8754 to better fit in display on boot [all platforms]
  • minor modifications on directory creation on startup [debian ARM]

[1.0.19-11] - 2018-01-29

Fixed

  • if dpkg reports failed state of fr24feed, try to repair on next run [debian ARM]

Added

  • OS version reporting for statistics purposes [all platforms]
  • unload DVB-T related kernel modules on fr24feed start [debian ARM]

Changed

  • redirect cron updater output to /var/log/fr24feed_update.log instead of /dev/null [debian ARM]

[1.0.19-8] - 2018-01-25

Fixed

  • binary permissions fixed according to user reports [debian ARM]
  • force dpkg to reconfigure bad state of fr24feed [debian ARM]

Added

  • http://RECEIVER_IP:8754/diagnostics_dump.tgz will download archive with diagnostics which can be shared with Flightradar24 support in case of something not working to facilitate diagnostics [debian ARM]

Changed

  • run as user fr24:fr24 instead of nobody:nogroup [debian ARM]

[1.0.19-6] - 2018-01-23

Changed

  • keep old versions in APT repository [debian ARM]
  • instead of taking ownership for /run/dump1090-mutability, just change permissions [debian ARM]

Removed

  • removed changing permissions for lighttpd log folder [debian ARM]

Fixed

  • removed writing to syslog by default [debian ARM]
  • when upgrading/installing in non-interactive mode (e.g. from crontab), answer APT questions with default values [debian ARM]
  • detect dvbt setting in /etc/fr24feed.ini by full line match, instead of by word [debian ARM]

[1.0.19-5] - 2018-01-19

Added

  • added support for systemd [debian ARM]
  • dump1090-mutability is installed automatically on fr24feed start [debian ARM]
  • enabled web-server map by dump1090-mutablity by default on ARM/Linux: http://DEVICE_IP/dump1090 [debian ARM]

Changed

  • in the installation script changed pgp.mit.edu to a pool of PGP servers [debian ARM]

Removed

  • removed support for init.d [debian ARM]
  • dump1090-mr removed from the fr24feed package [debian ARM]

Fixed

  • fixed a bug leading to no decoded callsigns in DF17 frames [all platforms]
  • SBS-3 messages were lost during decoding, resolved now [all platforms]
  • when specifying domain instead of IP for network data source, IP was resolved in the wrong byte order, fixed [all platforms]
  • fixed ARM64 SIGILL failures [debian ARM64]
  • fixed incorrect autoupdate detection in logs [debian ARM]

Security

  • run from nobody:nogroup instead of root [debian ARM]
  • install rtl-sdr.rules for udev to allow non-root user to access DVB-T hardware [debian ARM]
